SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 680
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Will Johnson of
Chuckey-Doak High School on being named to
the All-Region 1-3A Academic Team.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
excellence, have distinguished themselves in both their athletic and scholastic endeavors; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Will Johnson of Chuckey-Doak High
School, an athlete and scholar of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Johnson was recently named to the All-Region 1-3A Academic Team in
recognition of his superlative academic record; and
WHEREAS, Will Johnson epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he has
achieved a high level of success in sports and academics while evincing great character in his
every endeavor; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Johnson's notable achievements are a source of great pride for his
family, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Will Johnson's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate Will Johnson of
Chuckey-Doak High School on being named to the All-Region 1-3A Academic Team, wishing
him much success and happiness in his future endeavors.
